<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-11] XMLReporter crashes in testFailed when report.getThrowable().getMessage() is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-11</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;        String message = StringUtils.replace(report.getThrowable().getMessage(),&quot;&amp;lt;&quot;,&quot;&amp;lt;&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
        can be null if getMessage() on throwable is null.  This leads to the line:&lt;br/&gt;
        	failure.setAttribute(&quot;message&quot;, message);&lt;br/&gt;
        being called with message = null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible fixes:&lt;br/&gt;
        String message = StringUtils.replace(report.getMessage(),&quot;&amp;lt;&quot;,&quot;&amp;lt;&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
Instead of using the getMessage() on throwable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively, check that message is not null before writing that element to the xml (and write something different instead).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
